com.esri.mo2.cs.gdb
Interface CoordinateSystemSetTable

All Superinterfaces:
Cloneable, GeodeticTable, NamedObject
All Known Implementing Classes:
CoordinateSystemSetTableImpl
public interface CoordinateSystemSetTable
extends GeodeticTable

Represents a set of coordinate systems, for example, all the coordinate systems in US State Plane 1983. This set of systems (which is a table) usually groups these systems together because they share a common theme. The following is a coordinate system set table from the Geodetic Database:

  • [ARGENTINA, "Argentinian Coordinate Systems", Any, Any]
  • Zone I, "Zone I", "", CAMPO INCH, TM, DEGREE, METER, -72, -90, 1, 1500000, 0,
  • Zone II, "Zone II", "", CAMPO INCH, TM, DEGREE, METER, -69, -90, 1, 2500000, 0,
  • Zone III, "Zone III", "", CAMPO INCH, TM, DEGREE, METER, -66, -90, 1, 3500000, 0,
  • Zone IV, "Zone IV", "", CAMPO INCH, TM, DEGREE, METER, -63, -90, 1, 4500000, 0,
  • Zone V, "Zone V", "", CAMPO INCH, TM, DEGREE, METER, -60, -90, 1, 5500000, 0,
  • Zone VI, "Zone VI", "", CAMPO INCH, TM, DEGREE, METER, -57, -90, 1, 6500000, 0,
  • Zone VII, "Zone VII", "", CAMPO INCH, TM, DEGREE, METER, -54, -90, 1, 7500000, 0,
